ifconfig - interface configuration, view and configure network interfaces, things like your IP address, MAC address, and whether a network interface is up or down.
iwconfig - wireless interface configuration, used to view or configure Wi-Fi interfaces
netstat - network statistics, shows network connections, routing tables, listening ports, and traffic stats.
ss - socket statistics, modern, faster replacement for netstat
dig - domain information groper, DNS lookup tool.
mousepad - lightweight graphical text editor, basically a simple notepad-style editor.
echo - prints text or variables to the terminal, commonly used in scripts or to display environment variables.

